[h1]Phobos' Industrial Pathways: Biomass — Changelog[/h1]

[h2]v1.11.1 — PZ 42.15 Compatibility & Bug Fixes (2026-03-18)[/h2]

[h3]Bug Fixes[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]PZ 42.15.3 OnCreate crash[/b] — Fixed hard crash in all purity-tracked recipes caused by PZ 42.15 changing the OnCreate items parameter type. Recipes now use PhobosLib's iterateItems() for cross-version compatibility.
[*] [b]Tooltip error spam[/b] — Fixed ExceptionLogger stack traces when hovering over fluid containers (purity tooltip, fermentation tooltip). Replaced pcall-closure guards with pre-flight type checks.
[*] [b]Profession icon overflow[/b] — Resized Chemist and Pharmacist profession icons from 128x128 to 64x64 to match vanilla PZ profession icon dimensions.
[/list]

[h3]Changed[/h3]
[list]
[*] Requires [b]PhobosLib 1.30.0+[/b] (was 1.28.0+)
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.11.0 — Purity & Yield System Overhaul (2026-03-17)[/h2]

[h3]Changed[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]Multiplicative skill formula[/b] — Applied Chemistry skill now uses a multiplicative sliding scale (up to +44% at Standard Level 10) instead of a flat additive bonus. Configurable via SkillPurityInfluence sandbox option (None/Low/Standard/High).
[*] [b]Yield applies to PCP multi-output recipes only[/b] (Rule 1) — Lower input purity reduces output count only on PCP recipes with base count ≥ 2. Single-output recipes are unaffected.
[*] [b]Vanilla outputs no longer penalised[/b] (Rule 2) — Recipes producing vanilla items (matchboxes, fire starters, brain tan, etc.) always yield full quantity. Exception: blackpowder (flagship recipe).
[*] [b]±15% multiplicative variance[/b] — Purity results now vary ±15% to model real-world chemistry variance. Even skilled chemists can get lucky or unlucky.
[*] [b]YieldMultiplier sandbox option[/b] — Now correctly wired to the yield formula.
[/list]

[h3]Added[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]One-time rebalance notice[/b] — Players upgrading from older versions see a popup explaining the purity system changes.
[*] [b]Purity system rules documentation[/b] — Formalized design rules in docs/purity-system-rules.md.
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.10.1 — Trait Removal CTD Fix (2026-03-17)[/h2]

[h3]Bug Fixes[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]zReVaccin migration crash-to-desktop[/b] — The antibodies trait removal used player:getTraits() which does not exist on IsoGameCharacter in PZ Build 42, causing a CTD. Now uses the correct CharacterTraits API (getCharacterTraits → getKnownTraits → getName → remove).
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.10.0 — zReVaccin → ZVV Migration Tool (2026-03-17)[/h2]

[h3]New Features[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]Comprehensive save migration[/b] — New sandbox toggle (Maintenance / Reset > Migrate zReVaccin to ZVV) converts all zReVaccin 3.0 save data to Zombie Virus Vaccine equivalents:
  — 44 direct item mappings (zReLabItems → LabItems) + 2 vanilla fallbacks
  — ~20 items with no ZVV equivalent safely removed
  — 29 learned recipe transfers to ZVV counterparts
  — Antibodies trait removal with halo text notification
  — Scans player inventories (deep) and world containers in loaded cells
[*] [b]Bio-reactor workstation[/b] (experimental) — Powered CraftBench entity built from sheet metal, glass panels, clay pipes, and welding equipment (Metalworking 6). Gated behind PhobosLib experimental features toggle.
[*] [b]Custom furniture sprite pipeline[/b] — PZPK .pack compiler, binary .tiles compiler, tilesheet grid assembler, and sprite generation tools for creating custom tile-based furniture.
[/list]

[h3]Changed[/h3]
[list]
[*] Recipe count: 300 to [b]301[/b] (+1 bio-reactor construction, experimental-gated)
[*] Item count: 119 to [b]120[/b] (+1 Mov_BioReactor)
[*] Requires [b]PhobosLib 1.28.0+[/b] (was 1.20.0+)
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.9.0 — Item Model & Recipe Fixes (2026-03-16)[/h2]

[h3]New Features[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]Hemp Cheesecloth[/b] — New loom-craftable cheesecloth from hemp bast fiber. Accepted as a filter in tincture, oil pressing, and salt extraction recipes alongside vanilla cheesecloth.
[/list]

[h3]Bug Fixes[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]3D model references[/b] — Fixed ~75 items that displayed oversized placeholder icons when placed on surfaces (ground, tables, shelves). All 118 items now use correct vanilla 3D models: mason jars, bottles, clay jars, crucibles, cooking pots, and more.
[*] [b]Forged cooking pot model[/b] — Paper pulp forged pot items now use the correct forged pot ground model instead of the regular pot model.
[*] [b]Wildcard recipe inputs[/b] — Fixed several recipes that incorrectly accepted any item as input (tincture filtering, tar rope, oil pressing).
[*] [b]Press-dry recipe balance[/b] — Hemp press-dry recipe now correctly outputs 1 dried bundle per craft (5 sub-units = 1 whole bundle).
[/list]

[h3]Removed[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]Experimental FBX models[/b] — Removed 5 custom 3D model files and their definition script. Items now use vanilla models exclusively.
[/list]

[h3]Changed[/h3]
[list]
[*] Recipe count: 298 to [b]300[/b] (+1 hemp cheesecloth loom, +1 press-dry hand press)
[*] Item count: 118 to [b]119[/b] (+1 HempCheeseCloth)
[*] CI: Added StaticModel/WorldStaticModel validation against vanilla model allowlist
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.8.1 — Hemp Recipe Input Fix (2026-03-16)[/h2]

[h3]Bug Fixes[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]Hemp recipes now accept correct vanilla items[/b] — All 13 hemp retting and fiber extraction recipes (including hazard variants) now accept [b]HempBundle[/b] (fresh harvest) and [b]HempBundleDried[/b] (dried) instead of the unobtainable HempBroken item. Players can now use hemp directly from farming.
[*] [b]Wild hemp foraging[/b] — Updated to give HempBundle instead of HempBroken.
[/list]

